The paper deals with the problem of estimating the number of non-zero entries in a sparse boolean matrix product, which has applications in databases and computer algebra. This suggests that the paper could belong to the categories of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), Databases (cs.DB), Information Theory (cs.IT), Computational Complexity (cs.CC), or Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM). The paper uses techniques such as pairwise independent hash functions and sketching, which are commonly used in these sub-fields.
